This paper focuses on the design of measurement algorithms for programmable network switches, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the limitations and constraints of the switch architecture, which could be relevant to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The heavy hitter problem is a common task in network measurement, which could also place this paper under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of probabilistic recirculation to improve measurement accuracy could be considered a system-level optimization, which could place this paper under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of a specific algorithm, which could be relevant to the category of architecture (cs.AR).
